The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 BEML venture for mining

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT

 Hyderabad, May 26: Public sector utility Bharat Earth Movers Ltd has entered into a joint venture with Midwest Granite and Indonesias Sumber Mitra Jaya for contract mining in India, Indonesia, Australia and western Africa. 

 According to the agreement, BEML will be responsible for supplying equipment, spares and service required for mining. Midwest will undertake exploration, mining, development and production, while Sumber will provide expertise in large-scale coal mining. Midwest Granite is a private sector company engaged in mining, processing and export of natural stones. The Indonesian company is a mining contractor.

 While BEML holds a 45 per cent stake in the joint venture, Midwest and Sumber together own 55 per cent, BEML chairman and managing director V.R.S. Natarajan said.

 He said BEML had registered a profit of Rs 315 crore and its turnover was Rs 2,200 crore during last fiscal. In the current financial year, its turnover is expected to reach Rs 3,500 crore.




